learning_outcomes.en:
By the end of the course students
- can word the goals of teaching Estonian according to the national curriculum;
- know teaching materials and can create them;
- can plan and give lessons, considering the individuality of pupils, the possibilities of a modern learning environment, the principles of integration, special educational needs and the principles of formative assessment;
- can use different teaching methods considering teaching principles, the goals of study and the differences of learners
- can give supportive feedback to pupils.
